Following on from the 3.0 issue #280.  This is the config parser.

It is a basic top down parser.

We break the config into a list of tokens and travel through them to build
up a dict that corresponds to the config.

The parser allows:

* containers
```
    container {
        included_module 1 {}
        included_module 2 {}
    }
```
* nesting of containers
```
    container 1 {
        container 2 {
            included_module 1 {}
        }
        included_module 2 {}
    }
```
* many types including lists, dict and tuple values
```
    my_module {
        my_str = 'hello'
        my_int = 23
        my_bool = true
        my_list = [1, 2, 3]
        my_dict = {'x': 1, 'y': 2}
        my_tuple = (1, 'something')
        my_complex = {
            'list' : [1, 2, 3],
            'dict' : {'x': 1, 'y': 2}
        }
    }
```

We can cope with horrible stuff all on one line which I do not condone
```
group tz { cycle = 0 open = false volume_status { button_up = 4 button_down = 5 button_mute = 0 } time {} tztime la { format = "LA %H:%M:%S" timezone = "America/Los_Angeles" } tztime ny { format = "NY %H:%M:%S" timezone = "America/New_York" } tztime du { format = "DU %H:%M:%S" timezone = "Asia/Dubai" } }
```

If error are detected we:

* Inform the user about the error as best we can

```
general {{
        colors = false
}
CONFIG ERROR: Name expected saw `{` at line 1 position 9
```

Any module can declare itself as a container via our old friend class Meta
```
    class Meta:
        container = True
```

We try to cope with the config as well as we can if things are too bad we use a special error config so we can start and show the error in the status bar.


The process is two stage

1) parse the config into a general dict

2) parse that dict into a py3status config 

Hopefully having the two split helps.

To see the output as py3status gets it run `python parse_config.py <path-to-config>` in no config we try `~/.i3/i3status.conf`


I am aware of a few issues where the old parser accepted things eg
```
general {
        colors = false
}}
CONFIG ERROR: Name expected saw `}` at line 3 position 2
```
the old parser would be fine here.  As we get useful error that tell us the line/char and some basic issue, this should not be a major issue for users.

`i3status.py` changes include the  PR write_tmp_i3status_config() rewrite #248 which makes things look more complicated than they are.

Anyhow its here and I suspect it will need time to be assessed.  I will try to add a few more comments/docstrings especially around the processing for py3status `process_config()`

Please try to break it.

Fixes #1011 

This PR allows the user to span ForeignKey relationships with AutoSlugField's `populate_from` argument. It also allows the user use model methods in the `populate_from` argument. 

@trbs please let me know any feedback or suggestions? Thanks again for your work on this library, and for considering this PR!

This allows to automatically get a key of adequate size for the selected algorithm.

Resolves #50, depends on #58 

